Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.37,0:00:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I would find you here. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.87,0:00:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Joanna, my sister. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.87,0:00:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Please sit. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.01,0:00:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen to this: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.30,0:00:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“You are a holy people to Jehovah your God, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.81,0:00:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“and Jehovah your God \Nhas chosen you to become his people, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.39,0:00:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“his special property, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.69,0:00:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,out of all the peoples \Nwho are on the face of the earth.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.44,0:00:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The words of Moses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.44,0:00:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,speaking to our people \Nbefore they entered this land. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.45,0:00:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. \NAnd just before that, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.20,0:00:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,he told them to destroy \Nall the idols of the Canaanites. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.45,0:01:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder if there are more idols \Nin the land now than there were then. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.67,0:01:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,At every turn, \Nour people bow and pray to them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.38,0:01:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re doing all you can. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.09,0:01:11.18,Default,,0,0,0,,How dare you promote this filth! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.18,0:01:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But they don’t listen. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.26,0:01:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The true God . . . \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.01,0:01:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop right there. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.93,0:01:14.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I listen. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.93,0:01:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Moses came down from the mountain. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.93,0:01:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop talking. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.60,0:01:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think you’re great. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.02,0:01:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re like Elijah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.31,0:01:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m surprised Jehovah uses me at all. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.61,0:01:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I’m not. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.61,0:01:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You always want to do the right thing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.57,0:01:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It makes us proud. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.06,0:02:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonah! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.73,0:02:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonah! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.36,0:02:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Ye— \NYes, my Lord. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.36,0:02:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Get up, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.45,0:02:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,go to Nineveh the great city, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.70,0:02:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and proclaim judgment against her, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.54,0:02:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,for their wickedness \Nhas come to my attention. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.25,0:02:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Nineveh? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.46,0:02:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Nineveh. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.09,0:02:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They deserve to die. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.01,0:02:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s not his responsibility. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.92,0:02:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s just going to get himself killed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.13,0:02:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to talk to him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.14,0:02:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone needs to talk to him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.11,0:02:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve prepared a meal for you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.61,0:02:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m not hungry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.82,0:02:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,They haven’t spoken a word to me in hours. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.95,0:02:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Your brothers are young, Jonah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.49,0:03:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,The news you brought to us this morning \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.37,0:03:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,—it was heavy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.71,0:03:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What did your brothers say? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.13,0:03:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Izliah is afraid they will kill me; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.88,0:03:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,skin me alive. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.34,0:03:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn’t think they should even be warned. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.97,0:03:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Just let Jehovah slaughter them all. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.51,0:03:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And Eber doesn’t believe they will listen. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.68,0:03:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.14,0:03:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that if it’s Jehovah’s will \Nto destroy them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.73,0:03:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,he wouldn’t have commanded me to go. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.69,0:03:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But I do think Eber is right. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.40,0:03:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would they listen? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.65,0:03:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Our own people don’t listen. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.78,0:03:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet the warning still goes out. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.53,0:03:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But when has Jehovah \Never asked a prophet to go to a foreign land \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.62,0:03:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to preach judgment against it? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.17,0:03:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonah, I— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.75,0:03:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t have all the answers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.22,0:03:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,To be sent to declare judgment \Nin the heart of Assyria, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.55,0:04:03.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s unlike anything Jehovah \Nhas asked of his prophets to do before. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.56,0:04:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But if it’s Jehovah’s will \Nthat you should go, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.56,0:04:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,then you should go. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.23,0:04:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,He must have good reason \Nfor sending you there. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.90,0:04:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.61,0:04:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonah! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.61,0:04:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonah! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.61,0:04:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonah, look! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.66,0:04:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I got figs! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.08,0:04:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m going to pack you some cakes too. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.08,0:04:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I could go with you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.26,0:04:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Izliah is afraid they will kill me; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.93,0:04:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,skin me alive. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.73,0:05:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re leaving without saying good-bye? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.35,0:05:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You need to go back inside, Joanna. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.90,0:05:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But we had things prepared for you! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.11,0:05:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll need them in Nineveh. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.36,0:05:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re not going to Nineveh, are you? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.37,0:05:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Tarshish. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.08,0:05:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Jonah! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.24,0:05:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s the wrong way! \NGo back! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.79,0:05:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We can talk to Father! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.08,0:05:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Joanna! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.54,0:05:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t go to Nineveh. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.59,0:05:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I just can’t do it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.21,0:06:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But what will you do in Tarshish? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.92,0:06:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,When will you be back? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.59,0:06:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t know, maybe never. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.30,0:06:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Never? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.31,0:06:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Then who’s going to Nineveh? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.06,0:06:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Who’s going to tell them what Jehovah said? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.81,0:06:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sorry, Joanna. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.23,0:06:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t know what Jehovah will do. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.11,0:06:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But I just can’t do it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.11,0:06:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s too much. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.94,0:06:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn’t need me anyway. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.49,0:06:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We need you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.95,0:06:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And you’re Jehovah’s prophet. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.62,0:06:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re like Elijah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.99,0:06:29.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.62,0:06:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Not anymore. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.33,0:06:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Go home, Joanna. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.66,0:06:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sorry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.39,0:06:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,If it’s Jehovah’s will \Nthat you should go, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.39,0:06:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,then you should go. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.92,0:07:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Trust him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.17,0:08:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Look! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.68,0:08:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,By the gods. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.72,0:09:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Furl the sail! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.06,0:09:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Fasten those lines, men! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.56,0:09:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hatches! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.73,0:09:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Brace yourselves! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.83,0:09:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Secure the cargo! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.55,0:09:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn into the wave! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.35,0:09:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn into the wave! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.13,0:10:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain, we’re taking on too much water! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.84,0:10:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Throw the cargo overboard! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.30,0:10:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All of it! Now! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.85,0:10:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Get it over! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.48,0:10:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s no use! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.36,0:10:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,This storm is from the gods! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.44,0:10:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Baal! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.53,0:10:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Eshmun! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.53,0:10:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Melqart! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.16,0:10:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Help us! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.70,0:10:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Help us! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.87,0:10:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is the passenger? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.04,0:10:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s down below! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.88,0:10:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s down below. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.00,0:10:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Please! Save us! Help us!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.22,0:10:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you sleeping? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.47,0:10:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Get up, call out to your god! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.51,0:11:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps the true God \Nwill show his concern for us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.02,0:11:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and we will not perish. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.69,0:11:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Save us! Help us! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.69,0:11:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, help us, Melqart! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.07,0:11:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, help us! Baal! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.07,0:11:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Save us! Save us! Baal! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.11,0:11:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Deliver us! Baal! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.65,0:11:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s cast lots to find out \Nwho is to blame for this calamity! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.67,0:11:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s him! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.55,0:11:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Why has this calamity come upon us? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.59,0:11:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It is from the true and living God.  \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.01,0:11:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,He has brought this storm because of me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.27,0:11:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do you come from? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.06,0:11:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What is your country? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.35,0:11:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,From what people are you? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.69,0:11:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I am a Hebrew, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.90,0:11:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and I fear Jehovah the God of the heavens, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.19,0:11:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the One who made the sea and the dry land. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.19,0:11:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I am— \NI was his prophet. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.53,0:12:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What have you done? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.03,0:12:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He told me to go to Nineveh \Nand deliver a message. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.66,0:12:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, I ran away. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.29,0:12:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What must we do to you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.75,0:12:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to make the sea calm down for us?  \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.88,0:12:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What must we do? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.96,0:12:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Lift me up and throw me into the sea, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.76,0:12:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and the sea will calm down for you; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.63,0:12:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,for I know that it is because of me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.30,0:12:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that this violent storm has come upon you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.02,0:12:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s do it! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.73,0:12:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He’ll die! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.02,0:12:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If we kill Jehovah’s prophet, \Nwhat will He do to us?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.27,0:12:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If Jehovah wants him in Nineveh, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.44,0:12:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,won’t He be angered \Nif we throw him overboard? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.32,0:12:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Take to the oars, men. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.45,0:12:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Row for your lives! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.96,0:12:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s the land over there. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.13,0:12:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.59,0:13:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Row! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.64,0:13:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Row! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.22,0:13:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s no use. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.43,0:13:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to do what Jonah said. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.57,0:13:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, may we not perish \Nbecause of this man. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.58,0:13:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Do not hold us responsible \Nfor innocent blood, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.91,0:13:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,since you have done as you pleased, \NO Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.75,0:14:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He gave his life for us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.42,0:14:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Our gods did nothing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.97,0:14:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We should sacrifice \Nto his God for sparing us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.50,0:14:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,How am I still alive? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.17,0:15:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What will become of me? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.13,0:15:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,O Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.80,0:15:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the depths of the Grave, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.43,0:15:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I cry to you for help. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.35,0:15:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Please hear my voice. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.85,0:15:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I know I have been driven \Naway from your sight! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.48,0:15:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How will I gaze again upon your holy temple? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.28,0:15:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, may my prayer come in to you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.95,0:15:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,With a voice of thanksgiving \NI will sacrifice to you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.50,0:15:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What I have vowed, I will pay. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.16,0:16:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.16,0:16:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, are you OK? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.21,0:16:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.96,0:16:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Are there others? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.59,0:16:30.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re here to help. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.59,0:16:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What is your name? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.26,0:16:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.02,0:16:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Jonah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.31,0:16:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Grab his other arm; \Nwe need to get him to the house. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.88,0:17:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Papa says you are a prophet. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.13,0:17:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I was a prophet. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.97,0:17:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Papa says that you \Nwere swallowed by a big fish. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.14,0:17:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.72,0:17:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would a fish swallow you? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.43,0:17:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I was in the water. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.27,0:17:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why where you in the water? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.61,0:17:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I was on a ship; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.61,0:17:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,then I was in the water. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.90,0:17:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why were you on a ship? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.49,0:17:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I tried to run away from Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.04,0:17:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,When you were in the fish, were you scared?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.67,0:17:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.21,0:17:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you pray a lot? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.26,0:17:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.14,0:18:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you pray to God \Nif you were running away from him? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.90,0:18:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Father! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.07,0:18:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s Jonah! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.32,0:18:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s back! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.07,0:18:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonah! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.07,0:18:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Joanna. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.65,0:18:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I wouldn’t see you again. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.20,0:18:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you wouldn’t be back. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.24,0:19:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m so sorry, Joanna. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.70,0:19:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Please forgive me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.62,0:19:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Father waited for you to come home every day. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.50,0:19:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He never gave up hope. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.54,0:19:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.30,0:19:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,A fish? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.93,0:19:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,How is that possible? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.22,0:19:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a miracle, Izliah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.10,0:19:28.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah saved you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.81,0:19:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what will you do now? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.23,0:19:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t know. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.57,0:19:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it’s time \Nfor everyone to get some rest. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.33,0:19:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We can talk more tomorrow. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.95,0:19:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.37,0:19:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sorry about the things \NI said before you left. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.46,0:19:50.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t realize . . . \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.75,0:19:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s no matter, Izliah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.34,0:19:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,My decision to run was my own. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.55,0:20:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.85,0:20:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s good to have you back. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.94,0:20:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, thank you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.53,0:20:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.12,0:20:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m still proud of you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.37,0:20:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Sleep well, my son. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.25,0:20:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Father? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.17,0:20:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.17,0:20:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I can’t stop thinking \Nabout those men on that ship, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.92,0:20:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,all the cargo they lost, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.68,0:20:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the fear in their eyes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.72,0:20:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What if they didn’t survive? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.89,0:20:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I put them in danger. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.69,0:20:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Disobedience often hurts others, Jonah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.15,0:20:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,not just ourselves. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.07,0:21:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll pray for those men. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.45,0:21:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think Jehovah will ever use me again? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.24,0:21:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s shown you mercy, Jonah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.75,0:21:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He brought you home. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.87,0:21:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s be content with that for now. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.59,0:21:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Father, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.05,0:21:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sorry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.76,0:21:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, my son. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.76,0:21:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I know. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.14,0:21:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s try to get some rest. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.29,0:21:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Jonah! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.88,0:21:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,My Lord! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.30,0:22:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I am so sorry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.38,0:22:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I am so sorry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.43,0:22:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Get up, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.01,0:22:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,go to Nineveh the great city, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.64,0:22:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and proclaim to her the message \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.98,0:22:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that I tell you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.11,0:22:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.82,0:22:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.90,0:22:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.15,0:22:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I will do as you command. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.22,0:22:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,May Jehovah be with you, my son. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.81,0:22:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He saved me from the heart of the sea; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.31,0:22:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,he can save me again in the days ahead. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.73,0:23:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, I made these cakes for you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.95,0:23:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Joanna. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.99,0:23:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,How long will it take you to get to Nineveh? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.20,0:23:14.75,Default,,0,0,0,,If all goes well, maybe 40 days. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.75,0:23:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,May it go well. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.71,0:23:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.73,0:24:23.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you traveling to? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.73,0:24:25.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Nineveh.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.40,0:24:27.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.03,0:24:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just there.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.03,0:24:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.86,0:24:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I was selling some horses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.07,0:24:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll tell you this, \NI’m glad to be going home. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.20,0:24:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You should really be careful over there. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.83,0:24:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s what I’ve heard. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.83,0:24:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me about it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.25,0:24:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the city is huge. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.84,0:24:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It would probably take you \Nthree days to walk around it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.92,0:24:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The chariots\N—they’re the best in the world. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.05,0:24:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And the horses . . .\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.05,0:24:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.93,0:24:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The horses are magnificent. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.06,0:25:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the people? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.14,0:25:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The people— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.73,0:25:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They worship gods of war. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.98,0:25:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think they’re like? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.19,0:25:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,They love conquest and violence; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.03,0:25:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s like bread to them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.70,0:25:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s comforting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.91,0:25:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, don’t worry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.91,0:25:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Just don’t attract any attention to yourself. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.66,0:25:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Stick to your business,  \Nand you’ll be just fine. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.75,0:25:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What is your business anyway? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.55,0:25:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m a prophet of Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.89,0:25:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s sending me \Nto proclaim judgment against it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.85,0:27:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Same thing again? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.02,0:27:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s your fault! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.15,0:27:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello there, Foreigner.  \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.20,0:27:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are you going, Foreigner? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.88,0:27:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Stop! Stop! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.85,0:27:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,My food! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.06,0:27:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody help me! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.02,0:27:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.44,0:28:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the people? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.44,0:28:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They worship gods of war. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.11,0:28:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think they’re like? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.76,0:29:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,In—\Nin just 40 days more, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.47,0:29:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Nineveh will be overthrown. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.65,0:29:24.49,Default,,0,0,0,,In just 40 days more, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.49,0:29:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Nineveh will be overthrown! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.26,0:29:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Who’s the foreigner? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.01,0:29:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,In just 40 days more, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.22,0:29:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Nineveh will be overthrown! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.57,0:29:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In just 40 days more, \NNineveh will be overthrown. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.07,0:30:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Who can possibly overthrow our city? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.94,0:30:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Is he crazy? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.66,0:30:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He looks like an Israelite. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.70,0:30:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The true God has spoken. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.84,0:30:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The great violence of this city \Nhas come to the attention of the true God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.92,0:30:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, the true God, has spoken. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.22,0:30:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,This city will be destroyed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.93,0:30:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Nineveh will be overthrown. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.60,0:30:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah, the true God, has spoken. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.60,0:30:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Your city will be destroyed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.60,0:30:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,In 35 days, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.69,0:30:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,this city will be destroyed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.98,0:30:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Nineveh will be overthrown. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.44,0:30:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This city will be destroyed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.03,0:30:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We can’t just leave everything. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.37,0:30:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What should we do? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.62,0:30:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.62,0:30:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He is a prophet \Nof the Israelite God, Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.41,0:30:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What should we do? \NShould we flee the city? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.29,0:30:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We can’t just leave everything. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.00,0:30:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave our homes? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.38,0:30:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Where should we go? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.01,0:31:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.34,0:31:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If we repent, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.38,0:31:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe his God will have mercy on us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.35,0:31:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,According to the prophet, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.35,0:31:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,there are only 20 days left \Nuntil the destruction of the city. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.23,0:31:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Throughout the city, \Npeople are fasting and putting on sackcloth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.45,0:31:27.29,Default,,0,0,0,,They are asking the prophet \Nhow Jehovah wants them to behave, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.28,0:31:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and they’re trying to do as he says. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.53,0:31:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that what Jonah is telling them to do?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.91,0:31:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,No, the people simply reason \Nthat because there’s a warning \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.08,0:31:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and time before calamity strikes, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.08,0:31:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,maybe this God will change his mind. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.96,0:31:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What else have we learned about Jonah?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.51,0:31:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,A Ninevite reported \Noverhearing a conversation of Jonah’s. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.39,0:31:53.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems he originally chose not to come. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.35,0:31:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, he fled to Tarshish \Nbut was thrown overboard. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.77,0:32:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he claims Jehovah sent a fish \Nto swallow him and bring him back. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.44,0:32:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Is he insane? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.69,0:32:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe not. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.99,0:32:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This man speaks for the God of Israel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.62,0:32:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,—a God of miracles, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.62,0:32:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,known for his greatness and his power. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.99,0:32:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,He might be powerful in Israel, \Nbut we have our own gods here. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.00,0:32:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,True, but Jehovah is the one responsible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.96,0:32:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,for humiliating the gods of Egypt, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.13,0:32:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,even destroying their army in the Red Sea. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.47,0:32:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s also the One \Nwho brought about the great Flood \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.05,0:32:31.68,Default,,0,0,0,,mentioned in our histories. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.68,0:32:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He did this because the people of the time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.43,0:32:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,were extremely violent. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.15,0:32:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Call my scribe. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.90,0:32:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Help us, please! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.90,0:32:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Save us! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.24,0:32:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot accept gifts and bribes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.61,0:32:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has spoken. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.08,0:33:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,In 10 days more, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.87,0:33:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the true God will overthrow Nineveh! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.42,0:33:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The true God has spoken. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.51,0:33:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The violence of the city \Nhas come to the attention of the true God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.48,0:33:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The true God has spoken. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.85,0:33:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Nineveh will be overthrown. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.98,0:33:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The city will be destroyed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.45,0:33:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Hear the word of the king, people of Nineveh. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.74,0:33:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Hear the word of the king! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.08,0:33:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,“By the decree of the king and his nobles: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.50,0:33:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“No man or beast, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.67,0:33:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“herd or flock, should eat anything at all. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.05,0:33:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“They should not take food, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.47,0:33:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“nor should they drink any water. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.76,0:33:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,“Let them be covered with sackcloth, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.89,0:34:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,“both man and beast; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.48,0:34:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“and let them call out earnestly to God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.61,0:34:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,“and turn from their evil ways \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.73,0:34:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“and from the violence they practice. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.32,0:34:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,“Who knows whether the true God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.45,0:34:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,“may reconsider what he intends to do \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.28,0:34:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“and turn from his burning anger, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.83,0:34:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we may not perish?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.42,0:34:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In three days, \NNineveh will be overthrown! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.43,0:34:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has spoken! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.22,0:34:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Nineveh will be overthrown! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.35,0:35:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Something should be happening; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.27,0:35:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,there’s nothing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.56,0:35:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Would Jehovah actually pardon the city? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.49,0:35:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,No. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.53,0:35:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that’s not possible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.62,0:35:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How could Jehovah change his mind? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.58,0:35:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,What will these people think of me? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.58,0:35:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What good is a prophet \Nif his words don’t come true? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.21,0:35:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Was this not my concern \Nwhen I was in my own land? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.47,0:36:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why I tried to flee \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.72,0:36:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to Tarshish in the first place; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.81,0:36:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,for I knew that you are \Na compassionate and merciful God, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.27,0:36:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,slow to anger \Nand abundant in loyal love, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.48,0:36:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and one who feels grieved over calamity. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.07,0:36:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,O Jehovah, please take away my life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.78,0:36:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for it is better for me to die than to live. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.09,0:36:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it right for you to be so angry? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.18,0:36:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I must leave the city. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.10,0:36:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We know you are a prophet of the true God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.35,0:36:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We have faith that you speak truth. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.27,0:36:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, stay in our home. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.60,0:36:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,No. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.60,0:36:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We will make you comfortable. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.60,0:36:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I will not stay in this city. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.54,0:37:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Still nothing? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.72,0:39:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This plant grew so quickly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.27,0:39:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah still cares for me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.80,0:41:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,O Jehovah, let me die. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.64,0:41:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Take my life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.69,0:41:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It is better \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.53,0:41:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,for me to die than to live. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.57,0:41:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it right for you to be so angry \Nover the bottle-gourd plant? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.62,0:42:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a right to be angry, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.21,0:42:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so angry that I want to die. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.30,0:42:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You felt sorry for the bottle-gourd plant, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.93,0:42:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,which you did not work for, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.39,0:42:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,nor did you make it grow; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.76,0:42:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,it grew in one night \Nand perished in one night. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.35,0:42:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I not also feel sorry \Nfor Nineveh the great city, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.94,0:42:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in which there are more than 120,000 men \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.53,0:42:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,who do not even know right from wrong, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.20,0:42:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as their many animals? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.14,0:43:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you Jonah? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.47,0:43:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I am. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.68,0:43:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Mommy says you saved us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.48,0:43:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,No, Jehovah saved you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.11,0:43:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.40,0:43:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just a messenger. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.82,0:43:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.96,0:44:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.05,0:44:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve written about Nineveh \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.47,0:44:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,but also about Jehovah’s great mercy \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.22,0:44:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,both to the people there and to me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.06,0:44:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it hard to write about all that? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.61,0:44:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Painful. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.90,0:44:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what will you do now? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.53,0:45:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever Jehovah asks me to do. \N
